title: Product Designer
description:
Kapres Technology is looking for a Product Designer to work with a multinational client in the insurance sector. The product designer will work on the UX and UI part of the website of a very interesting project with medical-health objective, create figma designs, perform product discovery and create data visualizations especially with Power BI.
You will work together with the Product manager and team of developers.
 Requirements:
-3-5 years of experience as Product Designer
-High level of English
- Experience in data visualization, preferably with Power BI.
The offer is:
-100% telecommuting, although if you live in Barcelona or surroundings you can go to the office with hybrid or face-to-face mode if you wish.
-25 days of vacation.

title: Técnico Helpdesk - Deloitte Technology Madrid
description:
We are looking for a person eager to learn and develop in our Deloitte Technology team, with experience in the user support area to be part of this Firm. What will your day-to-day life be like?
- Remote connection to solve problems presented to the user.
- Opening of HP cases to repair physical damage to equipment.
- On-site solution of problems encountered by users (physical damage, accidents, software not working, software installation, UMTS configuration, etc.).
- Software installation.
- Configuration and installation of mobile devices (iPad, iPhone, cell phones, etc.).
- In the ticketing tool, assess which should be escalated to level 2 (problems that cannot be solved by the technician himself). How do we imagine you?
First and foremost, we are looking for someone who is eager to learn and find the best solution for the Firm's challenges as a team. Technically, you will fit the position if you meet these requirements:
- Advanced Technical Degree in Networked Computer Systems Administration or Intermediate Degree in Microcomputer Systems.
- Minimum experience of 6 months in a support technician position.
- B2 level of English.
requiredLanguage: Higher Level Training Cycle - Computer Science and Communications.

title: Programador/a Control en área BMS
description:
Funciones
Infojobs Performance, un servicio de Adevinta, selecciona un Programador/a Control en área BMS para importante empresa que se dedica a la consultoría e integración de IT.
Necesitamos incorporar en el área de operaciones, programador/a de sistemas de control con fabricante de referencia / plataforma trend control systems (Honeywell) o Schneider.
En dependencia de la Dirección de Área de Control de Operaciones, las funciones principales serán las descritas a continuación:
- Instalación de sistemas de control fabricantes TREND CONTROL SYSTEMS o SCHNEIDER.
- Documentación proyectos en este ámbito, interna y a cliente.
- Soporte técnico de mantenimiento.
- Diseño de soluciones de control en empresas.
- Interlocución con operadoras y empresas de servicio.
- Realización de informes de auditoría de comunicaciones y seguridad.
- Apoyo especializado para la realización de propuestas comerciales ofreciendo soporte al área de preventa.
- Cumplimiento de tiempos estimados para la resolución de cada tarea, ajustarse a los tiempos marcados.
- Resolución de incidencias en nivel 3.
- Programar herramientas destinadas a la eficiencia energética de edificios y/o data centers.
requiredLanguage:
FP Automatización y Control / Mecatrónica
Experiencia mínima de 3 años en programación e instalación de dispositivos de control BMS/ Conocimiento de la plataforma Trend Control Systems (Honeywell) / Schneider.
